[{"location":"api-reference/#API-Reference","page":"API Reference","title":"API Reference","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api-reference/#Reproject.interpolator-Tuple{AbstractArray, Int64}","page":"API Reference","title":"Reproject.interpolator","text":"interpolator(array_in, order::Int)\n\nReturns an interpolator with the given array and order of interpolation.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api-reference/#Reproject.pad_edges-Union{Tuple{Matrix{T}}, Tuple{T}} where T","page":"API Reference","title":"Reproject.pad_edges","text":"pad_edges(array_in::Matrix{T}) where {T}\n\nPads a given array and creates a border with edge elements.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api-reference/#Reproject.parse_input_data-Tuple{FITSIO.ImageHDU}","page":"API Reference","title":"Reproject.parse_input_data","text":"parse_input_data(input_data::ImageHDU)\nparse_input_data(input_data::Tuple{AbstractArray, WCSTransform})\nparse_input_data(input_data::String, hdu_in)\nparse_input_data(input_data::FITS, hdu_in)\n\nParse input data and returns an Array and WCS object.\n\nArguments\n\ninput_data: image to reproject which can be name of a FITS file,               an ImageHDU or a FITS file.\nhdu_in: used to set HDU to use when more than one HDU is present.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api-reference/#Reproject.parse_output_projection-Tuple{WCS.WCSTransform, Any}","page":"API Reference","title":"Reproject.parse_output_projection","text":"parse_output_projection(output_projection::WCSTransform, shape_out)\nparse_output_projection(output_projection::ImageHDU; shape_out)\nparse_output_projection(output_projection::String, hdu_number)\nparse_output_projection(output_projection::FITS, hdu_number)\n\nParse output projection and returns a WCS object and shape of output.\n\nArguments\n\noutput_projection: WCS information about the image to be reprojected which can be                      name of a FITS file, an ImageHDU or WCSTransform.\nshape_out: shape of the output image.\nhdu_number: specifies HDU number when file name is given as input.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api-reference/#Reproject.reproject-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"API Reference","title":"Reproject.reproject","text":"reproject(input_data, output_projection; shape_out = nothing, order = 1, hdu_in = 1, hdu_out = 1)\n\nReprojects image data to a new projection using interpolation.\n\nArguments\n\ninput_data: Image data which is being reprojected.               It can be an ImageHDU, FITS object, name of a FITS file or a tuple of image matrix and WCSTransform.\noutput_projection: Frame in which data is reprojected.                      Frame can be taken from WCSTransform object, ImageHDU, FITS or name of FITS file.\nshape_out: Shape of image after reprojection.\norder: Order of interpolation.          0: Nearest-neighbor          1: Linear          2: Quadratic\nhdu_in: Used to specify HDU number when giving input as FITS or name of FITS file.\nhdu_out: Used to specify HDU number when giving output projection as FITS or name of FITS file.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api-reference/#Reproject.wcs_to_celestial_frame-Tuple{WCS.WCSTransform}","page":"API Reference","title":"Reproject.wcs_to_celestial_frame","text":"wcs_to_celestial_frame(wcs::WCSTransform)\n\nReturns the reference frame of a WCSTransform. The reference frame supported in Julia are FK5, ICRS and Galactic.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#Reproject","page":"Reproject","title":"Reproject","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Reproject","title":"Reproject","text":"Implementation in Julia of the reproject package by Thomas Robitaille, part of the Astropy project.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Reproject","title":"Reproject","text":"This package can be used to reproject Astronomical Images from one world coordinate to another. By reproject we mean re-gridding of images using interpolation (i.e changing the pixel resolution, orientation, coordinate system).","category":"page"},{"location":"#Installation","page":"Reproject","title":"Installation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Reproject","title":"Reproject","text":"Reproject.jl is avilable for Julia 1.0 and later versions and can be installed with Julia built-in package manager.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Reproject","title":"Reproject","text":"julia> import Pkg; Pkg.add(\"Reproject\")","category":"page"},{"location":"#Usage","page":"Reproject","title":"Usage","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Reproject","title":"Reproject","text":"After installing the package, you can start using it with","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Reproject","title":"Reproject","text":"julia> using Reproject\n\njulia> result = reproject(input_data, output_projection)","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Reproject","title":"Reproject","text":"This returns a tuple of reprojected Image and footprint.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Reprojecting-Images","page":"Reproject","title":"Reprojecting Images","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Reproject","title":"Reproject","text":"To reproject Astronomical Images, primary requirements are Image data (2D Matrix), world cordinate frame of input Image and required output frame in which it needs to be reprojected.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Reproject","title":"Reproject","text":"The Image data and input frame is given together as an ImageHDU or FITS file or name of the FITS file in input_data. A keyword argument hdu_in can be given while using FITS or FITS file name to specify specific HDU in FITS file.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Reproject","title":"Reproject","text":"The output_projection is the output world coordinate frame and needs to be a a WCSTransform or an ImageHDU or FITS file or name of the FITS file. A keyword argument hdu_out can be given while using FITS or FITS file name to specify specific HDU in FITS file. WCS information is extracted from header when ImageHDU or FITS file is given as output_projection.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Reproject","title":"Reproject","text":"Order of Interpolation can be specified by keyword order (i.e 0, 1(default), 2). The dimensions of output Image can be given by keyword shape_out. This can be used to change resolution.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Example","page":"Reproject","title":"Example","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Reproject","title":"Reproject","text":"julia> using Reproject, FITSIO\n\njulia> input_data = FITS(\"gc_msx_e.fits\")\n\njulia> output_projection = FITS(\"gc_2mass_k.fits\")\n\njulia> result = reproject(input_data, output_projection, shape_out = (1000,1000), order = 2, hdu_in = 1, hdu_out = 1)","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Reproject","title":"Reproject","text":"Input Image:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Reproject","title":"Reproject","text":"(Image: community)","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Reproject","title":"Reproject","text":"Output:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Reproject","title":"Reproject","text":"(Image: community)","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Reproject","title":"Reproject","text":"Test files can be obtained from here.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Related-Packages","page":"Reproject","title":"Related Packages","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Reproject","title":"Reproject","text":"Check out AstroImages.jl, which use this package to form coloured RGB image from 2D CCD Astromonical Images.","category":"page"},{"location":"#License","page":"Reproject","title":"License","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Reproject","title":"Reproject","text":"The reproject package is released under the terms of the BSD 3-Clause \"New\" or \"Revised\" License.  The Reproject.jl package received written permission to be released under the MIT \"Expat\" License.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Reproject","title":"Reproject","text":"The authors of this package are aquatiko and giordano.","category":"page"}]
